The paper presents an algorithm for solving the Minimum Dominating Set problem using dynamic programming based on tree decomposition. This problem is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of tree decomposition also suggests that the paper may fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of parametrized algorithms, which are often used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for solving complex problems efficiently.
